caption: The Bum has me seriously bummed out. I own nearly all his books. I revere his importance in the hierarchy of Tiki gods when it comes to his bringing Tiki back to life. I had been looking forward to coming here since the opening. I suppose that I could grade 100% on the drinks. For that, Latitude 29 does a good job. However, these days a lot of places put together a lot of good drinks. Even if the bum was making it in the bar in front of me, it's hard to beat having Paul McGee make me drinks he'd been experimenting with in a bar that's multiple times as cool. Sorry dude. In one way, I can understand having big plate glass windows in front, but let's be honest, you only have to look at the pictures to see that the daytime shots are of a place that only marginally looks Tiki. The night ones look pretty good. We were quickly shunted into the boring side room. The drinks good. However, I never felt I was anyplace doing things other than by the number. For people not into Tiki enough to know who Jeff Berry or Paul McGee are, the drinks are great, but the atmosphere at many other places is better.

Great drinks OK service. My friends and I are huge tiki bar fans so we knew when we were in New Orleans we would have to make a stop here! The drinks were great be sure to try the (NAVY GROG) we were in town for the holidays so we got to try some of the sippin’ Santa menu so good. Would have given it five stars had our waiter Jeffrey not seem so irritated that we were there I will note that we got to the bar at around 8 PM so it’s not like it was last call, it really killed the fun relaxed vibe that we go to tiki bars for.
Wonderful,friendly ,helpful staff . Everything here has a nice flavor profile . It was very unique and the mushroom dumplings 🥟 were 🔥. Will return !
Modern tiki bar.

Best rum drinks in New Orleans! And that's saying a lot for a city who's signature drinks are hurricanes and rum punches. Their specialty drink menu is extremely impressive. Top shelf rums, local & imported. All the cocktails are very well crafted, no sugary mixes like the tourist spots on Bourbon. I've had the Rum Barrel, Pouka Punch, Latitude 29, and Jungle Bird, and they're seriously all top notch. Very nice vibe inside, low lit, tropical tiki bar feel. A great escape in the hot New Orleans summer. The bartenders are all friendly, and very knowledgeable. I thought I knew my rums, but they definitely taught me a thing or 2 lol. The food here is phenomenal. Possibly some of the best shrimp n grits in the 504, and I promise i'm not exaggerating. I've been back since covid, and they're definitely following all precautions to give you a safe feel. Tables are spread out & everyone is masked up properly. Always a great experience here, highly recommended!
The cocktails were amazing and the service was phenomenal!
By far my favorite bar.     Amazing drinks.   Great ambiance.  Pina Colada is by far the best in town!   I love this place.
Good drinks good service! Tasty cocktail
My favorite place to visit when in New Orleans
Great food and drinks
Very good. Excellent service and food. Great drinks. 5 star atmosphere.

Great spot for a unique selection of mixed drinks! A little bit of a quiet environment given all of the social distancing requirements but still a great vibe. The bartenders are very knowledgeable and will not disappoint.

The Pearl Diver and the whole experience changed me. I caught the tiki bug from this place and I can see why. The proprietor is a cocktail historian specializing in this type of mixology and establishment. Check it out. It’s a thing.

Beachbum Berry's Latitude 29 is a very fun tiki bar in the French Quarter. They specialize in reviving classic tiki recipes. When I visited, I was extremely impressed by the drinks and loved the food too. It was a great place to grab a drink and less kitschy than the bars on Bourbon Street. Overall, this is a place any tiki lover should stop!
Favorite tikki in no. Great decor and perfect drinks. The starters are amazing, especially the green beans. A staple of adventure when visiting New Orleans.
Frank Sinatra's cocktail was horrible, but the food was perfect.  Everyone at the Yankee finished every bite.  Of note: ribs and dumpling burger.
They have a wide array of tiki drinks and possibly the best tiki drinks I've ever had.
Pop up Santa was GREAT!!
Overall vibe is nice and the drinks are the perfect way to start a night in the French Quarter.
THE tiki bar to try in New Orleans.
Not very friendly
Legit tiki bar
Best tiki cocktails I've had in New Orleans, hands down. Extremely knowledgeable staff and a drink menu where you cannot go wrong. I wish I had more stars to give.
Best drinks in NOLA. their banana banshee is DELICIOUS. I never go to NOLA without stopping in for drinks here. Food is also great.
Some of the best drinks I've ever had... And I've been in bars on four continents.
great cocktails
Had a couple of great tiki drinks during happy hour. Will be back to try some others and maybe have dinner. Staff is very knowledgeable and helpful.
It was just Ok. The place was better a year ago.
OMG Who knew there would be such an authentic Hawaiian experience in  the French Quarter!!!. Matthew the bartender is an exceptional fella and a superb mixologist.
Great cocktails. Order from the small plates for variety.
Tropical rum drinks in a tiki bar. Appetizers are tasty. Happy Hour every day 3pm - 6pm.
Great drinks!
Hawaii 504 is so refreshing. And my god look at all those bitters
Good drinks nice bartender!
Favorite bar in New Orleans. Can't go wrong with any of their drinks.
Awesome drinks with good prices
Terrific tiki bar! The drinks were balanced, strong, and chock full of unique ingredients [guava, kiwifruit, etc.]. The rumki was an excellent appetizer and Sam, the bartender, is the man!
Top 10 US tiki bar. And got to meet the beachbum himself while we were there!!!
Get the loco moco or the shrimp and grits and get yourself whatever drink the bartender suggests.
The Navy Grog was delicious
Drinks are perfection.
Best drinks around!
Life changing tiki cocktails 👏👏
Different little hide away.  A visit to the Islands on the edge of the quarter.  Crafty Drinks and some Moco Loco

Amazing staff, perfect drinks, and a great atmosphere. Please do yourself a favor, stop in, enjoy the slowness, and order the most amazing Mai Tai you will ever have (None of this overly sugared sickly sweetness here).

Come here for the bar. The drinks are smashing and the bartenders are coreographed whirlwinds. I cannot stress enough how supremely talented and awesome they are. Every time I'm in Nola I visit this place and it is always a highlight of my trip. Get a few tiki drinks and some small plates. I don't know anything about the religious traditions of the various Polynesian peoples but I imagine this place is somewhere in the heaven/afterlife Pantheon.
Decor is awesome. Drinks are all a little too sour and not sweet (and overpriced) Food is good and reasonably priced.

A fun spot for a group! My partner and I only came as a couple and sat at the bar, which was very nice. We came early in the evening (around 530p) so it was pretty quiet.  Our bartender was friendly and made awesome cocktails for us. I had the Latitude 29 cocktail and my partner had one of the Christmas pop-up specials called the Surfing Santa. Both were delicious, and the pop-up menu items all came in funky fun glassware.  The atmosphere is signature tiki bar, which is perfect. All the lighting was fun to look at, and they had also added Christmas themed garnishes all around the restaurant which was super fun.
Fun Tiki bar.

An absolute must for tiki lovers. The drinks are tasty, the service was great and the glass case of tiki memorabilia was so cool. Like a tiny tiki museum. Definitely try the drink that you can get in the souvenir mug, it had the best little garnishes!
You like tiki drinks? Get up in here.
Amazing drinks a must if you're visiting New Orleans.
Awesome cocktails!!!
Your not worthy but it's there for you anyway. Food and beverage. Get on Larry's level.
They even made me my favorite tiki drink off-menu. Thank you. #yourockthetiki #painkiller 🍹🥥🌴

Tiki Drink Excellence!  What a great place to spend an hour or two with friends.  Every drink we tried was fantastic and exceeded our expectations.  Snack menu items were also delicious.  (We especially enjoyed the fries.)  Wonderful Tiki themed atmosphere.  Helpful and friendly staff.  Multiple seating options: cozy booths, regular tables/chairs, high tables, and a bar.  Clean restrooms.  Connected to hotel at rear of bar.  Parking was a little difficult to find, but we discovered the paid lot across the street.
Amazing cocktails and really good food. Get some!

Great drinks, but such poor service it's not worth it. I have  been so impressed with the great customer service received on holiday in the US, but staff in this bar were rude and unhelpful, and didnt seem to want us to be there.

Really not the best place if you're looking for a chilled drink! As a group of 7 we like a meeting point, the bar attached to the hotel seemed more than ideal. We tried this place 2 times and on both occasions the bar & serving staff were rude, laughed at us,  moved us from one table to another for no reason (even though the place was empty) then tried to move us back as all 7 of us arrived. Refused one of the group 2 drinks (own and partners and this was our 1st drink of the day). There are MUCH better places in the French Quarter to go. MY ADVISE....GO ANYWHERE ELSE.

This bar has the worst customer service I have ever experienced in the whole of America. It's a shame that it is attached to the hotel next door, as that hotel was so welcoming. I would never recommend this bar to anyone.

Always love Latitude 29! A super cozy, almost hidden tiki bar with unique cocktails. Special shoutout to the bartenders, they took the initiative to kick out a belligerent man that was disturbing us at the bar. Great staff and great drinks, as always!
Great drinks and awesome food. Right across the street from convenient parking
Excellent atmosphere. Great drinks

Very chill tiki place with excellent drinks. The bartender, Sam, was very knowledgeable about the drinks and helped us choose what to get based on what we liked. Will visit again while we are staying in New Orleans.
Mediocre drinks unfortunately
Fun times! Get the Lapu Lapu
Tiki cocktail
Best tiki drinks ever had!
A temple of a tiki bar.  Bartender knew her boat/island drinks backwards and forwards.  Look forward to visiting again and again.

Definitely felt like a Tiki bar when you went in.  PONTCHARTRAIN PEARL DIVER: An "iced buttered rum": our honey-butter-spice mix blended with passion fruit, lime and Jamaica rum - $12 *this is a very sweet and sour drink, didn't love the drink but did like my next one better plus it was on HH  MARTINIQUE SLING:  Fresh lime juice, lime cordial, Orchard Cherry liqueur, Martinique rhum, agricole vieux, dark Jamaican rum - $8 *citrus-y and rummy - great blend of sweet and tart  If I'm back in Nola, I'd love to come back for one of their more adventurous drinks like something with flames!
As far as tiki bars go, this one it’s really great. Inventive cocktails, fun staff, and thoughtful menu with just enough flare.
Fantastic tiki drinks with phenomenal menu options, and they're willing to make any common tiki drink off menu as well. I absolutely want to come back to NOLA just for this bar!

This is definitely not a place you'd expect to find in NO but I'm so glad we did. A classic tiki bar with all the flare and fun. A huge drink menu and food looked great even though we didn't get any. We visited twice and were happy both times.
Very quaint bar with great drinks and unique food

(Translated by Google) There are few menus so you only eat finger food. It's a good idea to relax with a Polynesian cocktail on a hot day. It would have been really nice if the menu was the same as before. Kimchi with Octopus seems to be a difficult menu in foreign countries  (Original) 메뉴가 거의 없어서 핑거푸드만 먹음. 뜨거운날 폴리네시안 칵테일로 쉬어가는것도 좋은듯. 메뉴가 예전처럼 있었다면 정말 좋았을듯. 옥토퍼스에 김치를 곁들어 준것이 외국서 보기힘든 메뉴인듯

Came in an hour before they closed and they did not seem happy to see me. The bartender was great. Made a good mai tai. The hostess made me feel unwelcomed. So I'm not sure I'll be back. Best of luck to the business.

Went to Latitude 29 based on a recommendation from a bartender.  I rarely drink, and when I do I prefer high quality craft options, Latitude 29 exceeded all of my expectations.  Devin (bartender) was patient with me as I deliberated which type of cocktail I wanted, and she made a fantastic Mai Tai, and provided excellent service throughout my stay, so much so that I brought three friends with me the very next evening.  Mention my name to Devin if you stop by and give her my best.
Amazing and authentic drinks, tasty appetizers.  The scallop rillette on the surf and turf board i could eat by the gallon.
Excellent drinks and excellent service! Steven, one of their main bartenders, is outstanding!

Just some feedback as a bar/restaurant owner. We were bummed about the service. The drinks are amazing but the staff at the front and servers are super short and rude. Still giving it amazing stars because we know how great of an influence you are in the industry. Hope to see a shift in culture and service at the front and tables that matches the bartenders. 👌🏻❤️
We will always love coming here!! The South Seas Sinner revamp is worth checking out. Not to mention everything else!
Drinks are exceptional! Mocktails are here! A locals fave!
These are as authentic "Tiki" beverages as you would get on any of the Polynesian islands. Steve is a cocktail wizard with his magic blender.
Great food

I am a tikiphile, so when I found a tiki bar while in NOLA for one day, I was excited. When I realized it was the legend BB's place I wanted to spend the entire time there! Great decor, superb, knowledgeable bartenders and delicious exotic cocktails! Will come backnto try the food!
Great classic Tiki drinks and fun atmosphere.

This is definitely like Mecca for me. I've been interested in Polynesian cocktails for a while and getting to Jeff Berry's bar was a real thrill for me. I went on a Sunday to take advantage of the happy hour and indulged in two cocktails, some chicken wings and some green beans. Both cocktails were absolutely delicious with the right amount of sweet, sour, and spice to make it nice. The green beans were a delight and the chicken wings cooked to perfection. The guy serving was a treasure and made the whole experience even better. What a great way to spend an afternoon!!

Fantastic immersive experience, loved all the decor and atmospheric touches. For cocktails I ordered the Banshee. Yummy: banana up front, and the dark rum hits you in the back. Beautiful presentation. Dinner was the cod, a really nice balance of textures and flavors, although portion was smaller than expected. Still, it was delicious. Was with a large group, and the service was attentive, patient, and very accommodating. Lovely people all around. Clean and charming establishment.
Awesome. Went in on a whim and was not disappointed.
This has been one of my Top 3 places to go in Nola for a long time. Consistency delicious, genuine and friendly service, and stand out bar program. Go here.

I stayed in New Orleans for 4 nights and came here 3 times.  The food is great,  but more than that, the drinks are just something that cannot be passed up. Huge fan of the rum barrel, navy grog and zombie. If in New Orleans hitting this cute tiki bar up is a must. So glad they have this.  It transports me back to the caribbean. Great selection of non-rums,  as well.  June 2019 update- Years later still great food and AMAZING cocktails.
Once you get past making a decision on what to drink and eat, everything is wonderful!

A Tiki bar that gets EVERYTHING right! Food, decor, the look....inch perfect. They've created a bar that stands out in a city known for it's bars and drinking! If this country had an ounce of common sense left to it they we'd elect Beachbum Berry KING.
Fun atmosphere and energetic and entertaining staff.  Dumpling burger was phenomenal!
Great friendly service. Hostess was very nice and showed drink specials . Food for everyone to enjoy

Theres a few skeptical reviews but I can honestly tell you to ignore them. This place is great. The food was very good. The drinks are a little pricey but the one we ordered was very good and strong. Made for a nice picture. I definitely recommend visiting here.
Huge variety of cocktails. Delicious food.
Great cocktails in a cool tiki setting.
Out of this world mixed drinks and cocktails. A fantastic alternative to your typical Bourbon Street drinks with a Polynesian take on things
Amazing drinks and incredibly friendly and knowledgeable staff!
(Translated by Google) Ho hum  (Original) Ho hum.
Yum. Drinks very good.
Great place before setting out into the quarter for dinner
Excellent tiki spot. All of the OG favorites. Everything was fresh and tasted great. A little tropical get away.

From the man who literally resurrected the tiki drink recipes you drink everywhere else, Jeff and Anene present the best tiki drinks in New Orleans hands down. The food is quite delicious as well. Not to be missed!
Tiiiiiikiiiii. Good drinks that look fancy too.
Amazing drinks, great staff. Love this place!
A little pricey but the food and drinks are really good and the atmosphere is awesome.

Our intro to tiki was a masterpiece of finely crafted rum cocktails. From old favorites like the Mai Tai to new twists, like the Ponchartrain Pearldiver, this is a must-visit for anyone who loves cocktails and scorns the pre-mixed syrupy stuff they sell at other bars in the French Quarter. Love their snacks, too, including the adobo!
Pure tiki magic!

I have been following the evolution of this establishment since before its inception. I finally had the opportunity to visit NOLA and experience firsthand the Latitude 29 experience. This is no ordinary bar, restaurant, joint. Every detail of this concept has been overseen with tremendous forethought and passion. There is truly no place else like it on earth. The proprietors managed to create a haven for ALL the senses. Everywhere you gaze, down to the most minute detail, brings you to the tropical paradise of your dreams. The feeling is intimate, relaxing and playful. You will not find a better cocktail, as every single recipe has been obsessively researched and finely tuned by the master, Beachbum (Jeff) Berry of Tiki culture infamy. The dishes are also thoughtful and current but equally matched to the libations. Presentation is key and does not disappoint. My scorpion bowl was a work of art, replete with a tiny mermaid lounging on a slice of lime. Mrs. Bum deserves good credit for her input in to this creative endeavor as well. It's a fine collaboration and a true partnership in what I can only hope will be the first of many to come.

On a short trip we visited twice because we had such a fantastic time just sitting at the bar chatting with the bartenders, drinking lots of tasty tiki drinks, and enjoying the decor. That being said, as a restaurant I would say that overall your experience would be lacking in the food department. Eat elsewhere and drink here many many times. 5 stars for the bar, less as a restaurant.
I’m sad because I really wanted to love this place. Drinks are  ok but 70%  ice. No thanks. We will go back to tiki Tolteca
Always fantastic, with a great happy hour.  Very well curated cocktails, as long as you like rum.
Went there for cocktails. Dark and dingy. Not much atmosphere but it was early. Perhaps it gets better later. Expensive drinks.

Solidly mediocre. Pork was okay, but lacked much flavor and was unimpressive. Cauliflower was not cooked totally through, but the rice underneath was good. On the positive side, the fruity drinks were decent. Much better food options in the Quarter but may be worth a stop for a fruity drink.

Been to New Orleans many times to eat and drink, and never even heard of this place before it was in Forbes as 20 must see bars BEFORE I DIE.  Regardless, glad I made it. Was greeted promptly and seated at table even though we were only having drinks.  Server was prompt, knowledgeable and effecient. She explained many of her favorites and guided us very well.  Seasonal Christmas menu was just introduced this day too.  Drinks were well presented, tasty and structured. Someone put some serious planning into them and trained staff properly too. There was a small mishap with drinks, but amended quickly...even before we noticed.  We have a few tiki bars in Las Vegas, but they need to take some lessons immediately from Berry.  Well done. Will return because of all your components:  Drinks, service and ambiance.  Thank you!!!

The hostess was so rude, the service was horrible. First time in New Orleans and this was by far the worst service we had. The fries were good but that is all I can say. We spent a lot of money in that bar to be treated the way we were. I would never recommend this bar to anyone.
True tiki. Not much match for sale
Great tiki bar, great drinks, I wish it was cheaper I would live there. Still not a bad value for the great drinks
We only drank, but the drinks were something special and authentic.  Recommend.
Delicious, authentic, and strong drinks. Friendly service and knowledgeable bartenders. Delicious small plates and great atmosphere. Will definitely be back every time we visit!
Modern tiki at its finest! Great drinks, friendly staff, and a totally modern take on tiki. I love it!
Happy hour was very happy indeed. Id come back in a heartbeat.

Love to come here for delicious hand crafted drinks. For food they do have a couple options that can be made vegan! I’ve always had excellent service and last time I went they had a great happy hour going on!
Great cocktails and food
Wonderful selection, great drinks. Everything is fresh squeezed and delicious. I highly recommend the short rib appetizer. Everything was perfect from start to finish.

I had a great time here, the drinks were delicious and fun and the staff was friendly and offered us various recommendations on where to go next! Only issue was it was sometimes hard to know who our server was/ who to put in an order with as everyone was interacting with us.
Great food, fan cocktails, fantastic service.
Drinks are exquisite and the bartenders  are characters. Get the Kea Colada with  Macadamia, tastes like liquid Key Lime Pie.
Great atmosphere and drinks!
Charming tiki bar with traditional mugs and tropical drinks.

Pretty good food; they offer a unique selection that isn't very common to the area. There are plenty of drinks although I found them to be okay and perhaps a bit overpriced but that is something the French Quarter is known for. All in all not a bad place.
Great place to indulge in the tiki vibe! Wonderful cocktails & food!
#tiki

Nice atmosphere and good service. The drink menu is large but more island style sweet rum drinks which are not my favorite. If you like those type of drinks this is your place.  I didn't try any food so cant comment on that...

If you love tiki or just fun, great drinks and a festive atmosphere, this is a must-visit. The best spot to sit is definitely the bar but those seats are usually the first to go since you get to see what the bartenders are up to. Fun tiki mugs and delicious classic tiki drinks to match. But don't forget to also have some food. That Loco Moco and hot buttered rum really hit the spot when I went in during a 44-degree winter night.
Drinks are absolutely amazing and out of this world! Great service!

Have been wanting to go here for quite sometime and finally made my way to New Orleans for a business trip and decided to stop in. Such a great place to sit back and unwind, high five to Pearl Divers!

Thoroughly enjoyed our experience - fantastic cocktails by a very capable bartender - I tried the seasonal rum-based Kris Kringle and a gin-based Island Outcast - both fantastic. Noshed on taro chips and sampling platter - the corn salad was fabulous. This tiki bar was far more warm and comfortable than my expectations - most welcome!
Good food too!

The 'Bum saved from oblivion many of the original recipes of Don the Beachcomber and Trader Vic. He and his staff live up to the highest craft cocktail standards(and yes, Tiki was the original craft cocktail movement) while bringing the unique warmth and conviviality of New Orleans to the experience. I'll see you there!
New Orleans' best tiki bar. A true original - the real deal.
One of sour, two of sweet, three of strong and four of weak... absolutely incredible tiki establishment. Don't miss this hidden pearl that makes bourbon streets drinks taste like watery Kool aid
Great tiki bar, great drinks, bartender was very knowledgeable and friendly
Great find! Wonderful drinks and great food!

Our waitress was awesome, but you're super limited to options for food - and if you're a picky eater like I am, good luck! Husband got a drink that seemed to be one of their most popular drinks. $18 for a decent sized drink but the taste.. I couldn't swallow the sip I took of it. I don't know how he finished, besides just not wanting to be rude. Maybe it's just not our vibe, but I had much higher hopes.
Love the tiki vibe, great cocktails and super snacks/small plates. Happy hour seven days a week.
Amazing drinks and awesome atmosphere!
Big Easy tiki!
Yummy drinks!

Heard about this bar from one of the bartenders at The Polynesian in New York. The staff is very friendly, the cocktails are so creative and the menu is huge. They serve delicious food as well (especially the taro chips). I did not even know before going there that this bar was created by a legend, Jerry "Beachbum" Berry. If you go to NOLA you should definitely step by Latitude 29. You will not regret it!

I came here because of Wayne Curtis's "And a Bottle of Rum, a History of the New World in 10 Cocktails," originally just to get a variation of Don the Beachcomber's Zombies. However, it was so much better than just a pilgrimage.  This was one of the few places I've been where they have a rum list (of amazing rums!), and not just a whiskey list. The cocktails were AMAZING, and the food was perfect for complementing the cocktails.  Our bartender Kim was funny, attentive, and incredibly knowledgeable. My wife had no idea what she wanted, but knew her tastes. Based on that, Kim suggested several cocktails she loved.  I can't recommend this place enough, whether for experimenting, drinking, pilgriming, or just having a good time, Latitude 29 has everything you need!
Cool spot with fantastic cocktails.
One of the best tiki bars in the world. The bartenders are extremely knowledgeable and passionate about their craft, but also down to earth people. Such a fun place!
Took some friends here. Drinks are great and very unique. Not like anything you'll find in other bars in New Orleans.

I love Tiki. And I love Berry's books. But I didn't love this place. It was my #1 must-do during our trip, and I was disappointed. To be fair, the drinks were actually quite good. And if I had stopped there, I probably would have given it 4 or 5 stars. But I made the mistake of ordering food. It was massively over-salted. And I mean massively - I am not salt adverse by any means. And even if it wasn't, the food just wasn't on par with literally everything around it. I mean, it is New Orleans - one of the greatest eating towns in the world. Why would you eat something that doesn't live up to that reputation when you can go 20 yards in any direction and do so much better?
Great drinks, service and ambience
Octopus & rum!
Meh. I ready wanted this place to be better.
Great drinks and a very cool atmosphere. Don't forget to buy a tiki mug for your collection. Beach bum Berry is a legend!!
Very creative drinks in an 'authentic' tiki bar environment.  Great selection of rums as well.
Great drinks, very tropical atmosphere
Incredible drinks, great place to cool off, and very friendly staff. Also the inside is decorated pretty cool with a Tiki theme.
Best dark hidden treasure chest of a bar, great island menu
My wife had a few drinks befor we went to burbon street. They did not have any domestic beers.

I have food allergies to coconut. Everything I tried to order I couldn't get because yours drinks you use coconut to stir or shake with or utensils have been used in coconut I guess you can't wash or use clean ones. I tried to order chicken wings but since your use foods with coconut and dont use different grease to cook in I couldn't eat. Everyone who has ever worked in kitchen or has a chef certification or degree or manager of the kitchen would know  how to handle food allergies and preparation of food.

If you have never been to a good (or real) tiki bar you do not need to miss this place. The back wall in the bar is impressive. The drinks are quite good. Tiki Bars are their own culture. The drinks prepared here are exotic and nuanced in their perpetration. The food is above you normal bar food. If Kim is there, ask for her. She has been awarded mixologist of the year...
Service ,food and drinks all superb . Decor was great and loved the tiki vibe.

The best meal and drinks I've had in NOLA. I'm so happily surprised. We are trying to think of a better meal we've had from coast to coast and having a difficult time. NYC to DC to Cleveland to Chicago to Tampa to Minneapolis to Seattle to Portland to LA...then Hawaii and Alaska. This is one of the tops. Thanks to chef and staff for an enjoyable time!
Can't go wrong with anything you order here. Matt was an awesome bartender who was very sweet. Great time and worth all the money
I love this place. Fabulous drinks, fun decor and friendly bartenders.
Awesome tiki drinks. This place also has rare and fine rums by the glass. The founder won a Spirited Award for his book about tiki drink history.
Pretty RAD place! Their deco, music and the way they plate their dishes and prepare their drinks is also beautiful. Now as for their tropical flavors,  let's say that it is soooooo good!
Super fun place to share some Tiki drinks with your friends.
This is my favorite tiki bar in New Orleans. The drinks are always beautifully made, and the staff is very nice. They have really cute kitschy decor that adds to the vintage tiki bar feel.

If you want to go to a place in the French Quarter that serves incredibly fine cocktails from the tiki tradition, this is it. They basically invented or reinvented the modern Tiki culture that has spread across the country. They also have one of the finest rum selections and some of the most knowledgeable bartenders anywhere.
Living next to the old Don the Beachcomber it's hard to give any other tiki bar a 5, but the staff is super friendly and make great drinks.
Great space right off N. Peters. Amazing, unique cocktails and our bartender was super knowledgeable and made great recommendations.
Awesome Tiki drinks and the food is top notch too.
Exquisite, authentic; a genuine delight, but at a dear cost. Drink to enjoy, linger with good company, and you will have a great time.

Great tiki drinks, at least the two I had. The first drink was the Nui Nui, a classic tiki drink brought back from obscurity by Jeff Beachbum Berry. The drink was citrus forward, sweet but not syrupy, and delicious. The second drink was a Mississippi Siren, similar in flavor profile but a tad more tangy, maybe do to having tamarind. This was a vodka drink. The place was very welcoming and Beachbum Berry was nice and willing to interact.
Great drinks and awesome food. But best of all the bartenders are the best.
Not enough people appreciate what Jeff Berry has done. I love this place and I go back whenever I can.

Delicious cocktails and virgin drinks were perfect to cool down after an evening tour. Staff was friendly. We were there at closing and it took a little while to get our checks, even though it wasn't busy.
Amazing Tiki drinks and great staff
This is my favorite bar in the city, hands down. The drinks are well put together with fresh ingredients and the staff always makes me feel like a "regular".
Awesome cocktails, low-key spot to get away from the crazieness of the French quarter.
Tasty drinks. Awesome fries 😄

Bartenders were very personable and helpful in choosing their wide array of drinks. Visited twice during our stay and each time did not disappoint. The drinks were strong, tasty, and had beautiful presentation. Absolutely worth the stop!

Tiki Bar in the heart of the French Quarter. Their Tiki drinks have been uncovered, rediscovered, perfected and created by Jeff Berry. Decor is perfect, owner makes a point to talk with customers. I had the Pontchartrain Pearl Diver which was beautifully presented and delicious. Bought his new book and he signed it. Loved this place. One of the highlights of our New Orleans trip.
Loved the drinks!!!
Beautiful, fun restaurant. Great decorations!
Amazing tiki selection and care that goes behind each cocktail. Thrilling atmosphere and chill vibes!

This is a true Tiki-Bar in the style of the old Trader Vics. They have a full bar with a wide selection of rums from around the world. They also have a full kitchen, but we only went for drinks.  Their menu has the classic Tiki cocktails and a few non-traditional ones made with liquors other than rum. They even have one or two made with Gin. I only ordered one Tiki drink. For the life of me, I don't remember what it was. It may have been a Zombie. All I remember was it was good.  We also sat at the bar here. The bartender knew his stuff quite well. He designed some of the drinks himself. In the past, I have been a big rum drinker and switched to whiskeys and bourbons in the past couple of years. Since they had such a wide selection of rums, I asked for a recommendation of a sipping rum. I can't tell you what he gave me, but I do remember it was dark and aged 12 years. It was very smooth. One of the choices we discussed was a French rum. He schooled me on the differences between French and other rums. Apparently, the French have very strict regulations about what goes into their rums. For example, the sugar cane has to be pure. He gave me a sample of one and it had a very different taste than the Island rums I'm used to. It is not quite as sweet and is much smoother. I am not sure if I liked it as much as the Island rums, but it was good.  Another good choice of location. But, since it is a themed bar, and kind of kitschy, it is one you need to really want to try before you go there. The experience is different than a more traditional bar.
Food is great and drinks are great. Atmosphere is unique and staff super cool and friendly. A must do if in the area
Great food and great cocktails.
Located in Burnsville house hotel

My friend and I were looking for something different to try, and we could not have been more pleased. It was DELICIOUS. The pork adobo was something I’ve never experienced before. If you like strong drinks, this place is even better. The banshee was delicious and refreshing. If I could give them more than 5 stars, I would.
The food and cocktails are soooo good i’m dead
Undoubtedly the best tiki bar and polynesian restaurant in New Orleans. Get there immediately and order a rum old fashioned.
Hands down best Rum bar in New Orleans
Everything is slow there. But the drinks are good. Get the Rum Barrel.
Great drinks, good music. Matt, the bartender, was awesome!

The pork adobo is phenomenal.  The mixed drinks are good too (especially if you love rum and/or communal drinks 🍹 🍸) but what really stood out was the food. The green beans were an excellent appetizer. My wife and I will certainly be back as this was the best meal we’ve had since we’ve been here.

My new favorite place in NOLA.  Outstanding, Amazing, Fantastic, and that doesn't even do it justice.  Drinks were perfect.  I was torn because I wanted to have more of each Drink, but every new cocktail I tried was just as good.  The food was on point too!
Best zombie outside of California
The best! If you come to nola and don't come here you are doing it wrong
Love the tiki vibe in here, makes for a memorable experience along with the cocktails that follow!
Won't let children under 7 inside.
Awesome sharable plates, well balanced tiki drinks with something for everyone. Great atmosphere; tiki without feeling kitschy. Shout out to our awesome waiter Steve!
My favorite bar anywhere in America. It's as close as I get to having a home base when I'm in New Orleans.
Great place, didn't try the food. Good drinks.
The drinks are fantastic.
Great atmosphere. Fun bartenders.
Perfect, as expected and wonderful staff, food and drinks!! Hi-5's!!
My wife and I love this place. Best tiki cocktails that we have had in NOLA.
Fantastic drinks and great atmosphere.

Great cocktails from an experienced bartender. The pearl diver and mai tai were excellent...tasty drinks, beautifully presented and keen attention to flavors and details. Nice atmosphere. Happy hour posted online wasn't correct. Starts 3pm not 1pm

Simply one of the very best The food was delicious and drinks were a class act with superb mixology and garnishes alike  I wish they were open later.  They close real early

Very nice - avoid the heavier ones other than the pins colada guy and focus on the fun juicy versions. Happy hour is fine, especially the fries! Love both sauces: sriracha aoli and a very tangy kimchi ketchup. Bring friends, as slurping out of a big bowl is always a special experience. Friendly cool bartenders too.
Awesome Tiki bar in the corner of the French Quarter! Their take on a Pina colada is fantastic!

One of my favorite spots in New Orleans. The space is modern tiki- a romantic spot for a date, a fun space for a small group. The staff is friendly, attentive, and educated on their food and drinks. I had the Pearl Diver - a delicious frozen buttered rum. My friend had the Rum Barrel and said it was delicious but lethal! One drink was enough! While fantastic  drinks are to be expected at this lovely tiki bar, the food was the stand out. The burger is one of the best I've ever had in New Orleans. It was cooked to perfection, moist, and would make a Big Mac weep with jealousy. The kimchi ketchup tastes fantastic with the  fries. My friend took our server's suggestion for the Pork Adobo. She said the pork was cooked perfectly and the coconut was a surprising addition to a delicious dish. 5 stars arent nearly enough!
Food was boring, drinks were ok

Anyone who knows Beachbum Berry (or his reputation) knows the cocktails will be killer, and they are, but the surprise is how novel and tasty the food is. Recommended for real dinner and/or small plates.
This place was great! I enjoyed the hand made cocktails a ton. I will definitely be taking my out of town friends here

Understated tiki decor with spot-on details. Great cocktails, happy hour deals, and seasonal specials - wintery cocktails put us in the Christmas spirit. Souvenir mugs and other swag available to take home. Expert bartenders and servers prove this is a must-see for any tikihead.

Best service we had the whole time we were in New Orleans. Food and cocktails were amazing! The cocktails are so unique and they were all good. Good vegetarian options. I had the Green Curry, vegetable dumplings, and vegetable poke (which is nothing like poke). For drinks I had the Zombie and the Island of Misfit Toys.

This place was the beginning of an addiction. We first came here a couple of years ago because my fiancé thought the drinks would be right up my alley...turns out we both fell in love with the rum combinations so much we stocked our own home tiki bar and of coarse returned the night before our wedding! We recommend this bar to everyone going to NOLA and credit it with our tiki addiction! Thank you Latitude 29! P.S. The app with the recipes is worth the download!
